<DOCNO> XIE19960201.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-36 21:00 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Suspends Aid to Niger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 31 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. administration
announced here today it had suspended economic and military
assistance to Niger as a response to the military coup on Saturday
that overthrew its duly elected government.
</P>
<P>
The United States will not recognize any military-appointed
replacement and calls for the military leadership in Niger to
immediately restore the elected government, the White House said
in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"The existing democratic institutions, however imperfect,
represent the will" of the people of Niger and must be respected,
the White House said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. economic development and military aid to Niger totaled
25 million dollars in the last fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Some army officials took power in Niger, ousting President
Mahamane Ousmane and Prime Minister Hama Amadou and installing
Army Chief of Staff Ibrahim Barre Mainassara as the country's new
leader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
