<HEADLINE> Iran Expels Bahraini Diplomat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran tonight announced the
expulsion of a Bahraini diplomat following the worsening relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
An Iranian Foreign Ministry official said that Ali Ebrahim
Al-Sisi, second secretary in the Bahraini embassy in Tehran, was
asked to leave Tehran within one week.
</P>
<P>
The official was quoted by Iran's official news agency IRNA as
saying that the expulsion of Al-Sisi is a consequence of his
involvement in matters which is against the diplomatic norms.
</P>
<P>
However, the report gave no detail about his involvement.
</P>
<P>
The relations between Iran and Bahrain have worsened recently
since Bahrain, for the first time, publicly accused Iran of
involvement in the political unrest in Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain last month accused Iran of stirring up 13 months of
Shiite Moslem protests in the Gulf Arab state.
</P>
<P>
But Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati denied the accusation.
</P>
</TEXT>
