<HEADLINE> UN Chief Dismayed by Colombo Bomb Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 1 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Boutros Boutros-Ghali on Thursday expressed shock at a violent car
bomb incident in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
"The Secretary-General is dismayed by the loss of life
resulting from Wednesday's bomb incident in Colombo," said a
statement issued by the spokeswoman of Boutros-Ghali, Sylvana Foa.
</P>
<P>
Foa said the secretary-general deplored acts that target
civilians and stressed the need to find an early negotiated
political solution to the conflict in Sri Lanka which continues to
inflict great suffering and losses on the country.
</P>
<P>
A truck packed with explosives rammed into the central bank in
the heart of Colombo's financial district on Wednesday, killing 53
people and wounding 1,4000 others.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the explosion was the work of Tamil Tigers
who have been fighting for an independent homeland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
