<HEADLINE> Nigerian Army Begins Training Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian army has begun a
series of training designed to keep its troops in good shape all
the year round, according to the assistant director of army
public relations, Lt.-col. Felix Chukwuma.
</P>
<P>
The training program, Chukwuma noted on Wednesday, was
designed in phases to span the whole year and ensure that each
armyman was in combat readiness.
</P>
<P>
The program commenced a few weeks ago with a medical check-up
for all army officers and soldiers to ensure that they were
medically fit and sound.
</P>
<P>
The army spokesman dismissed suggestions that the involvement
of the military in government might affect their fighting
ability, explaining that only a very small number of officers
have been involved in direct governance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
