<HEADLINE> Seeiso To Succeed As Lesotho's New King On January 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Prince David Mohato
Bereng Seeiso of Lesotho will succeed the crown of the southern
African kingdom on February 7, reliable sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Lesotho Prime Minister Ntsu Mokhehle said the
government has already set the date. But he refused to reveal
when.
</P>
<P>
Seeiso will succeed his father the late King Moshoeshoe II who
was killed in a car accident two weeks ago when his car veered
off the mountain road.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old prince reigned as King Letsie III during his
father's exile to Britain in 1990.
</P>
<P>
But he was dethroned in November the same year by the military
government and his eldest son reigned until January 25, 1995 when
he abdicated in favour of the restoration of his father. 
</P>
</TEXT>
