<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac Says France Ends Nuclear Test "Once and For All" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 1 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques
Chirac today promised the U.S. Congress that France has finished
its nuclear testing "once and for all".
</P>
<P>
"France has finished once and for all its nuclear testing after
a final series designed to give us the assurance that our
deterrent capability is reliable and safe," Chirac said when
addressing the joint session of the U.S. Senate and House of
Representatives.
</P>
<P>
Chirac arrived here on Wednesday for a two-day state visit, the
first of its kind by a French President in the last 12 years.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that France is willing to joint the other major
nuclear powers to "promote disarmament and combat the
proliferation of weapons of mass destruction".
</P>
<P>
France announced the decision to end the nuclear test on
Monday, two days before Chirac's visit to Washington. But some
U.S. Congressmen, who boycotted Chirac's speech, said that it was
too late to win their applause. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
