<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Allots 2.5 Million Dollars To Fishery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Agriculture announced today that 16 million birr (about 2.5
million dollars) has been alloted towards fishery resource
development activities in the country.
</P>
<P>
Tarekegn Mengistu, fishery resource development team head of
the ministry, said beneficieries of the fund would be fishermen
and businessmen engaged in fish trade in the form of credit
service.
</P>
<P>
Problems hindering the exploitation of fish resources are now
being tackled step by step, he said, adding the country's efforts
to attain food self-sufficiency have got financial support from
the European Community.
</P>
<P>
The achievements include boat maintenance workshops,
laboratories, shops and other facilities under construction in
different towns and around lakes, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's annual fish production potential is estimated at
25750 tons. However, only 5,340 tons are reported being
exploited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
