<HEADLINE> Rebels' Attack On Vehicle Leaves One Dead In S.  Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, February 1 (Xinhua) -- One man was killed and two
others seriously wounded when the car in which they were
traveling from Bo, southern Sierra Leone, to the capital ran into
a rebel ambush early today, local journalists in Bo said.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred at Senehun, 24 miles from Bo. The
vehicle left Bo at 3:00 am this morning when it ran into a
roadblock in the middle of a bridge, the journalists said.
</P>
<P>
The ambushers opened fire, killing the civilian on the spot.
The civilian has still not been identified, one journalist said.
</P>
<P>
This is the first ambush on the highway since the rebel
Revolutionary United Front announced a week-long ceasefire which
ended yesterday.
</P>
<P>
There is still no word as to whether the ceasefire is
continuing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
