<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 17:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria To Erect More Plazas On Highways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian federal government
is to erect more toll plazas on highways in the country to
generate more revenue for the maintenance of roads.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Works and Housing Minister Abdulkarim
Adisa while talking to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) today in
Bauchi, northern Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
NAN quoted Adisa as saying that the plazas would be erected on
roads leading to tourists centers, citing the Yankari Games
Reserve in Bauchi and the Obudu Ranch in cross river.
</P>
<P>
He said that the federal government's decision to privatize
the 28 toll gates in the country was to generate more revenue.
</P>
<P>
He explained that up to 75 percent of the money collected at
the toll gates were not paid to the government, because officials
of the ministry that collected the tolls were more interested in
enriching themselves than paying money collected into the
government purse.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot continue to allow this unpatriotic act to continue
so we decided to hand over toll collection to private persons,"
he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
