<HEADLINE> Sudan Expresses Regrets over US Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Sudan today expressed its
regret over a U.S. decision to withdraw its diplomats from
Khartoum.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released here, the Sudanese Foreign Ministry
said the U.S. decision was taken at a time when the two sides
embarked on a serious dialogue to tackle issues tampering with
bilateral relations. It described the decision as lacking
realistic and positive reasons.
</P>
<P>
The statement called upon the U.S. government to reconsider its
decision for the best interests of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Clinton administration had officially notified Sudan of its
decision Wednesday evening, citing security reasons.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources here maintain that the United States will
open a representative office in a neighboring state adjacent to
Sudan in order to maintain contacts between the two countries.
</P>
