<HEADLINE> US Troops Launch Drills in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 3,900 U.S. troops
today began maneuvers focusing on weapons and air coordination
support in the Kuwaiti desert.
</P>
<P>
The troops, including marines, sailors and support personnel,
took part in the exercises intended to demonstrate the commitment
of the United States to maintaining security and stability in the
Gulf, according to a statement released by the U.S. embassy here.
</P>
<P>
The exercises are seen as a deterrent to Iraq, which invaded
Kuwait in 1990 triggering the the Gulf crisis. Kuwait and the
U.S. signed a 10-year defense agreement after the coalition forces
headed by the U.S. drove Iraqi troops out of the emirate in
February 1991.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti troops, however, are not participating in the
exercises. 
</P>
