<HEADLINE> Greece's Shipping Exchange Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Inflows of shipping exchange in
Greece totalled 1.6211 billion u.s. dollars between January and
September 1995, marking an increase of 18.7 percent over the same
period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to Bank of Greece figures released today, in August
and September, inflows of shipping exchange were relatively low
compared with the previous months, which increased by just 1.6 and
0.8 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Greece's merchant fleet has grown steadily during the last two
years and is now ranked third in the world, accounting for 6.5
percent of world tonnage, and first in the European Union with
half of all vessels under EU flags. 
</P>
</TEXT>
