<HEADLINE> UK Public Sector Pay Likely to Rise 4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 1 (Xinhua) -- British Cabinet is preparing to
approve pay rise of up to four percent for 1.4 million public
sector workers.
</P>
<P>
Local press reported today that the increase, greater than the
inflation rate of 3.2 percent, are expected to be approved by
ministers next week and in force from the beginning of April.
</P>
<P>
Although the rises are higher than the government had expected,
ministers want to avoid a confrontation with public sector groups
such as doctors, nurses and teachers in what could be a general
election year.
</P>
<P>
A cabinet minister said on Wednesday night that the recommended
increases were "uncomfortable". But he was confident that they
could be financed from within existing budgets. 
</P>
