<DOCNO> XIE19960201.0039 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 16:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ice Blocks Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Ice has caused havoc on a stretch
of the Yellow River in northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Since January 26 ice has blocked the river's course in Dali
County, pushing up the water level, breaking the embankments in
several places and causing widespread flooding.
</P>
<P>
The local government is making every effort to minimize the
problems. Already thousands of endangered people have been
evacuated to safe places, and the Qingtongxia Reservoir on the
upper reaches of the Yellow River has closed its gates so that no
more water will flow to the disaster-stricken area.
</P>
<P>
The Lanzhou Military Area Command has sent engineers and air
support to smash the ice blocking the river. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
