<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 16:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Tourism Trebles In Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 1 (Xinhua) -- International tourism to
Zimbabwe has more than trebled over the past five years, Zimbabwe
Council for Tourism Chairman David Chapman said here today.
</P>
<P>
He said that tourism earnings between 1990 and 1995 in
constant price terms increased from 428.8 million Zimbabwe
dollars (47.6 million US dollars) to 799.7 million Zimbabwe
dollars (88.9 million US dollars) in 1995.
</P>
<P>
He added that the overall picture indicated that travel and
tourism accounted for approximately 11 percent of all economic
activities throughout the world, making it the world's largest
industry.
</P>
<P>
He also said investment in tourism, because the industry
tended to be labor-intensive, usually produced more jobs than
investments in other activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
