<HEADLINE> Cyprus Pepsi Taken Over by Local Breweries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- A local company, Photos
Photiades Breweries that produces Carlsberg beer, has bought the
franchise for the Pepsi Cola and Seven Up company in Cyprus with
11.5 million Cyprus pounds (about 23 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Pepsi franchise was held until today by Loizos Louca
Sons Ltd, which produces fruit juices.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the "Photos Photiades Group of Companies"
said that the take-over, which comes into effect today, was
motivated by future prospects in view of Cyprus' accession to
the European Union.
</P>
<P>
"Expanding and upgrading our operations is part of our
efforts to prepare to meet increasing competition," the spokesman
added.
</P>
<P>
He said that the group is already exporting Carlsberg beer
and bottled water to Lebanon and is currently negotiating a
similar deal for the Greek island of Rhodes.
</P>
<P>
The Photiades group outbade another local brewery, Keo, which
produces a beer bearing its name.  
</P>
