<HEADLINE> China's Largest Cashmere Company Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, February 1 (Xinhua) -- China's largest cashmere product
company was founded this month in Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region, one of the world's major cashmere suppliers.
</P>
<P>
The company, the Erdos Cashmere Product Co., Ltd, at present
boasts an annual production capacity of 510 tons of cashmere
material, 1.50 million cashmere sweaters and 330 tons of cashmere
yarn. Its products are sold to more than 30 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The company's predecessor, the Erdos Cashmere Sweater Plant,
registered sales totaling 745 million yuan and post-tax profits of
151 million yuan last year, according to a survey report by Arthur
Anderson &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
The company has its stock listed on the B-share market of the
Shanghai Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
This year the company will purchase five cashmere-processing
factories, import advanced technology and equipments and expand
the production base for raw materials. 
</P>
