<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Reports Large Growth in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Shaanxi Province in northwest
China has reported a major growth in foreign trade over the last
five years.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that the foreign trade volume of the
province totalled 6.8 billion US dollars-worth from 1991 to 1995.
</P>
<P>
In this period the province exported 4.86 billion US
dollars-worth of goods, which was three times the figure for the
previous five years.
</P>
<P>
The province now has trade ties with 123 countries and regions
worldwide. Its major export products include machinery, electrical
appliances, textile and light industry products, and coal and
related technology.
</P>
<P>
In the same period the province approved 2,052 foreign
investment projects, involving 3.33 billion US dollars in agreed
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
It actually used 1.51 billion US dollars of overseas capital,
which was three times the figure for the previous five years.
</P>
<P>
The province also saw an improvement in the structure of its
foreign investment in the same period. About 70 percent of its
overseas investment is in the fields of industry, infrastructure,
resources development and agriculture.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
