<HEADLINE> Polish President Names New Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Polish President Aleksander
Kwasniewski this morning appointed deputy parliament speaker
Wlodzimierz Cimoszewicz as prime minister and asked him to form a
new government.
</P>
<P>
According to the PAP news agency, the president said that
Cimoszewicz, supported by the ruling coalition of the Democratic
Left Alliance and the Polish Peasants' Party, was "well prepared"
for the job and has a chance of winning strong support in
parliament.
</P>
<P>
Cimoszewicz's appointment follows the resignation of Jozef
Olesky over espionage allegations, which Oleksy has denied.
</P>
<P>
Cimoszewicz Thursday told reporters that he would try to form a
government by next week and would do his utmost to win the support
of parliament. He said he expected most ministers would maintain
their posts.
</P>
<P>
He added that he would continue the economic policies of his
predecessor, but would put more stress on law enforcement.
</P>
</TEXT>
