<HEADLINE> hke020162--Manila to Execute Death Convicts with Lethal Injection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government will
execute death convicts with lethal injection.
</P>
<P>
The Senate today approved on second reading a bill prescribing
lethal injection as the means of executing death convicts.
</P>
<P>
The bill will amend the measure restoring the death penalty and
 replace the method of carrying out the capital punishment by
electric chair or gas poisoning.
</P>
<P>
At least 120 convicts have already been sentenced to death in
the lower courts and are awaiting the decision of the Supreme
Court.
</P>
<P>
However, since the country has no electric chair and the
construction of a gas chamber is too costly, the Senate and the
House decided to simply employ lethal injection as the means of
execution.  
</P>
</TEXT>
