<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Protects Foreign Businessmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, February 1 (Xinhua) -- This special economic zone
will continue to give priority to cracking down on misdeeds
affecting foreign businessmen in a bid to protect their interests
and boost their investment confidence.
</P>
<P>
Last year Shenzhen paid special attention to cases of harm to
foreign businessmen, assigning special detectives to such cases,
solving 130 major cases harming Taiwan entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
They also listened to the opinions of Hong Kong and Taiwan
businessmen and took effective measures to improve public security.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the number of serious criminal cases dropped by
1.8 percent in 1995. That was the first time in the past eight
years that there has been a drop in such cases, a local police
officer said today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
