<HEADLINE> Russian Coal Miners Stage Nationwide Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, FEBRUARY 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 500,000 coal miners began a
nationwide strike today, demanding payment of their delayed wages
and sufficient government backing of the coal industry.
</P>
<P>
A total of 118 of Russia's coal mines and 27 of its 83
open-cast strippings have joined the strike with the production
and shipment of coal were suspended in 87 percent of the country's
coal mining enterprises, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin's economic aide Alexander Livshits "got
in touch" with Chairman of the Russian Coal Miners' Union Vitaly
Budko this morning, Interfax reported without giving any details.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Interfax, Livshits said "a tough monthly
schedule" for payments to coal miners is being compiled this year
on the president's instructions. He added that the Finance Ministry
transferred the last 600 billion roubles (more than 130 million
U.S. dollars) to the miners on Wednesday as repayment of Last
year's debt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
