<HEADLINE> Kodak to Sell Latest Photo Products in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Kodak Company of the United
States intends to sell a complete line of advanced photo system
(APS) products under the new "Kodak Advantix" brand in China
during the second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Victor Chan, Kodak's chief representative
in China, at a news conference held here today.
</P>
<P>
The full line of APS products includes nine types of cameras,
three types of film and high-speed photofinishing equipment, all
of which are designed to make photography easier and increase
people's enjoyment in taking pictures.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from Kodak and other world-renowned photography
product makers show that about 150 million US dollars-worth of
film is wasting annually worldwide.
</P>
<P>
APS products, a joint effort between Kodak and Japan's Canon,
Fuji, Minolta and Nikon companies, have eliminated the problems of
exposure mistakes.
</P>
<P>
APS combines innovative film, camera and photofinishing
technologies to provide many benefits requested by customers.
</P>
<P>
Having first sold photography products in China in 1927, Kodak
has set up six liaison offices as well as more than 800 service
centers in the country.
</P>
<P>
Last year Kodak's sales volume rose by more than 50 percent
over the 1994 figure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
