<HEADLINE> Myanmar, Sri Lanka Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 1 (Xinhua) -- An agreement on the
establishment of a joint commission for bilateral cooperation
between the Myanmar government and the Sri Lankan government has
been signed here, according to a joint press release today.
</P>
<P>
The press release was issued at the conclusion of Sri Lankan
Foreign Minister Lakshman Kadirgamar's four-day visit to Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
It said the two sides expressed great satisfaction at the
successful visit of the Sri Lankan foreign minister to Myanmar
which has opened a new chapter in bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan foreign minister, accompanied by officials and
some 22 businessmen, arrived here Monday.
</P>
<P>
He was received by Chairman of the Myanmar State Law and Order
Restoration Council and Prime Minister Senior General Than Shwe.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan foreign minister also held talks with his
Myanmar counterpart U Ohn Gyaw on bilateral, regional and
international issues. Both ministers expressed the desire to
further strengthen the traditional ties of friendship and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official statistics, Sri Lanka's
investment in Myanmar amounted to one million US dollars as of the
end of last November.
</P>
<P>
The volume of trade between Myanmar and Sri Lanka was about one
million US dollars in 1994. Average value of import from Myanmar
was 41 million US dollars in the fiscal years from 1990-91 to
1993-94, while export to Myanmar was almost none for that period.
</P>
<P>
