<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 14:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sexual Hygiene Shop to Shut Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- China's first sex shop, the
Beijing-based Adam &AMP; Eve Health Center, dealing in contraceptives
and products relating to sexual hygiene, is about to shut down as
a result of rampant fake products.
</P>
<P>
The center, established three years ago, has won a good
reputation among consumers.
</P>
<P>
Its sales volume has kept rising, topping three million
yuan-worth in 1995, manager Qiao Yue said.
</P>
<P>
To date, China has 517 special shops of this kind and 3,778
counters marketing sexual hygiene products in other shops.
</P>
<P>
The gross sales of such products stood at 1.1 billion yuan last
year.
</P>
<P>
The center is the second-largest sex shop in China in terms of
sales volume, next to the "Garden of Eden", its competitor in the
capital.
</P>
<P>
But fake products constitute a big threat to their development,
Qiao said, adding that the market for sex products is "in chaos".
</P>
<P>
The shop would take the way of "suicide" in order to draw the
public's attention to the ill-managed market for sexual hygiene
products, Qiao warned.
</P>
<P>
But, observers here still have doubts about it.
</P>
<P>
It is learnt that the government has drawn up rules for the
better management of this sector, and they will come into effect
this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
