<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 13:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU-Ukrainian Trade Agreement Takes Effect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Interim Trade Agreement
between the European Union (EU) and Ukraine took effect today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement provides for reciprocal most favoured nation
treatment whereby the EU and Ukraine will lower tariffs on each
other's products.
</P>
<P>
Non-discrimination against foreign products and liberalization
of capital transfers will be guaranteed under the agreement, which
was signed in Brussels in June 1995.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also abolishes quantitative restrictions on some
products, except for Ukrainian textiles and steel. But higher
quotas will allow Ukraine to export more textiles and steel to the
EU in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The EU is Ukraine's main trading partner outside the
Commonwealth of Independent States, with two-way trade volume
amounting to nearly 3 billion European Currency Units (about 3.8
billion U.S. dollars) in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
