<HEADLINE> Moderate Recovery for Bulgarian Economy in 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria's inflation rate
dropped to 32 percent at the end of 1995 from 122 percent at the
beginning of the year -- the biggest achievement for the year-old
government of prime minister Zhan Videnov.
</P>
<P>
Along with plummeting inflation, interest rates fell from 72
percent in early 1995 to 34 percent by year's end.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Bulgaria's foreign trade surplus has reached 500
million U.S. dollars, the first surplus since 1989 when the
Eastern European country underwent drastic political changes.
</P>
<P>
The country's GDP in 1995 increased 2.5 percent over the
previous year and its foreign exchange reserve came up to 1.3
billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
