<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The opposition Forum party of
Zimbabwe has called for an all-party constitutional conference to
work out a new constitution and electoral act ahead of the
presidential elections.
</P>
<P>
In a statement on Wednesday, the party's secretary for
publicity and information James Dzvova said that if such a
conference was not held, the presidential elections would be ''a
mere farce''.
</P>
