<HEADLINE> Israel Deports Suspected Palestinian Spy to Jordan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Israel today deported to
Jordan a West Bank Palestinian who was arrested on suspicion of
spying for Iran, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Mohammed Salameh Mohammed, 44, who holds Jordanian
citizenship, was deported via the Allenby Bridge crossing over
the Jordan River this morning.
</P>
<P>
The General Security Service (GSS) revealed on Wednesday that
Mohammed confessed that he was drafted into service by Iranian
intelligence about one year ago by a staffer at the Iranian
Embassy in Jordan.
</P>
<P>
He also told GSS investigators that he had managed to provide
Tehran with Israeli maps on which he marked military
installations and government offices.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested in the home of relatives in Bethlehem in
November, before the Israeli army withdrew from the city. He had
arrived from Jordan in October to visit family.
</P>
<P>
"Iran, Syria and other Arab countries have been making a
great effort to obtain intelligence information on Israel, and
the Iranian effort has been intensified recently," a senior
Israeli security source said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Israel considers Iran as the country which poses greatest
threat to its security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
