<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan President Condemns Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga today condemned the rebel Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) for resorting to terrorism.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, she said, "the LTTE has once again
resorted to mass destruction of life and property within the city
of Colombo."
</P>
<P>
She said, "the LTTE has also resorted to act of desperation at
the time when they suffered major military setbacks at the hands
of the security forces and the government's peace proposals to
resolve the ethnic problem has resumed the acceptance of the
majority of the Tamil people."
</P>
<P>
She said, "the LTTE's action is clearly intended to derail the
peace process by provoking some people to cause harassment of
innocent Tamil citizens."
</P>
<P>
"This unfortunate incident once again reminded us that
terrorism must be firmly dealt with," she said.
</P>
<P>
She said the situation now has been brought under control and
the Central Bank has recommenced its operation.
</P>
<P>
The bomb blast carried out by the LTTE on Wednesday morning had
damaged several high buildings and left about 100 people dead and
more than 1,200 injured.  
</P>
