<HEADLINE> Chinese, HK Officials Hold Sixth Informal Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Government officials
and senior Hong Kong civil servants held their sixth informal
get-together here today.
</P>
<P>
At a news briefing after the meeting, Yuan Pengyan,
secretary-general of Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch, said
that the sixth informal get-together was a success.
</P>
<P>
He said that up to now, more than half of the senior Hong Kong
civil servants with ranking 5 and above have participated in the
get-togethers which started at the end of last November.
</P>
<P>
He said through exchanges, the participants at the
get-togethers now have a better understanding of the principles
and policies of the Central Government of China toward Hong Kong,
including "one country, two systems" and "Hong Kong people running
Hong Kong", and stabilizing the ranks of civil servants in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that he believes the exchanges in the coming months
will result in more consensus between the two sides and enhance
the civil servants' confidence in Hong Kong's future.
</P>
<P>
He noted that more get-togethers between the two sides will be
held in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that the get-togethers have achieved its objectives and
the results of the meetings agree with the consensus reached by
the Chinese and British sides.
</P>
<P>
Eight Chinese government officials and five senior Hong Kong
civil servants participated in today's meeting.  
</P>
