<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Completes Billion Dollar Public Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Department of
Public Works and Highways (DPWH) completed infrastructure projects
worth 28 billion pesos (1.1 billion US dollars) in 1995.
</P>
<P>
According to DPWH 1995 year-end report, of the total projects,
10 billion pesos represented carry-over work from 1994 while 18
billion pesos were for 1995 projects.
</P>
<P>
Among the projects completed last year, the highways category
posted the biggest value at 15 billion pesos. The flood control
category came second with 2,100 projects costing a total of 3
billion pesos.
</P>
<P>
This was followed by the rural water supply category with a
total cost of 846 million pesos. These projects contributed to a
16 percent increase in the rural population served with potable
water to 25 million last year.
</P>
<P>
The DPWH has a proposed capital outlay of 25 billion pesos for
1996. Of the sum, 10 billion pesos are reserved for
foreign-assisted projects while 15 billion pesos are intended for
locally-funded projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
