<HEADLINE> Seles Moves into Quarter-final at Pan Pacific Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Monica Seles, who was
plagued by shoulder injury, cruised into the quarter-finals of the
Pan Pacific women's indoor tennis tournament on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Seles, playing her first match since she won the Australian
Open, defeated unseeded Romanian Irina Spirlea 6-4, 6-2, in 65
minutes.
</P>
<P>
"The court is so much faster than at the Australian Open, and
I didn't play for a few days because of my shoulder," she said.
</P>
<P>
Spirlea, 21, double-faulted at the end of the ninth game of
the first to give Seles a decisive break and the Yugoslav-born
American then coasted to victory.
</P>
<P>
Seles takes on eighth seed Iva Majoli of Croatia in the next
round. Majoli defeated Brenda Schultz-McCarthy of the
Netherlands 7-6 (8-6), 7-5.
</P>
<P>
In other second-round matches, 15-year-old Swiss Martina
Hingis had an easy win over Ai Sugiyama, beating the unseeded
Japanese 6-0, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, the youngest Australian Open quarter-finalist in the
Open era, next meets Japan's Naoko Sawamatsu, who upset
fourth-seeded compatriot Kimiko Date on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain had a walkover
into the quarter-final following the withdrawal of Australia's
Nicole Bradtke who injured a foot in the doubles on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Eighth seed Lindsay Davenport, who lost to Seles in the final
of the Peters International championship in Sydney earlier this
month, scored a convincing 6-1, 6-3 win over fellow American Lisa
Raymond.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old's quarter-final opponent is second seed
Conchita Martinez. 
</P>
