<HEADLINE> Philippines-Brunei Air Services Agreement Ratified </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Philippines President Fidel
Ramos today retified the air services agreement between the
Philippines and Brunei Darussalam.
</P>
<P>
The agreement establishes air srevices between and beyond the
two countries and reiterates specific aviation rights embodied in
the convention on international civil aviation.
</P>
<P>
Both the Philippines and Brunei Darussalam agreed that the laws
and regulations relating to immigration and customs requirements
by one contracting party are made applicable to the other
contracting party.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will take effect on the day of the exchange of
diplomatic notes between the Philippines and Brunei Darussalam.
</P>
