<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Leaves for Asian FM Meeting of Asia-Europe Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen left here today for Phuket, Thailand,
to attend a meeting of Asian Foreign Ministers, a preparatory
meeting of the Asia-Europe Summit to be held in Bangkok on March
1-2.
</P>
<P>
At the routine press conference this afternoon, Foreign
Ministry spokesman Chen Jian described the summit as an important
attempt for enhanced co-operation between the two continents of
Asia and Europe at a time when international relations are
undergoing profound changes and a trend for multi-polarization is
being accelerated.
</P>
<P>
China has adopted an active and earnest approach toward the
summit and hopes that it would help improve the mutual
understanding and co-operation between the two continents and play
a positive, constructive role in creating a new type of
Asia-Europe partnership.  
</P>
</TEXT>
