<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia Sets up Nature Reserve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region is building a nature reserve in the northern Dahinggan
mountains to protect the original ecology and carry out scientific
research.
</P>
<P>
The reserve covers 107,000 hectares in an area of high latitude
frozen earth zone with the tree coverage rate reaching 82.8
percent, and has kept intact the ecological system of a primitive
coniferous forest.
</P>
<P>
It abounds with 332 species of plants, 30 types of animals
and 106 kinds of birds including red-crowned cranes, mooses and
gluttons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
