<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 09:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Market Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
dropped from Wednesday's two-year high due to profit taking today.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries index dropped 3.4 points to 2,285.1 points.
</P>
<P>
Local dealers said that the local market was still in good
shape. Expectations of a US interest rate cut boosted the local
bourse to its highest level since February 8, 1994 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Reserve of the United States lowered official
interest rates overnight. The news pushed up the New York Stock
Exchange by 13.73 points to 5,394.94 points.
</P>
<P>
Local dealers said that the Australian market had already been
set on the expectations and that today's consolidation was quite
normal.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrials index lost 14 points to 3,440.3 points,
while the All Resources index rose by 5.2 points to 1,411.6
points.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 216.29 million shares, valued at
529.79 million Australian dollars (392.04 million US dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
