<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended
slightly firmer against the greenback today.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended at 74.57 US cents from 74.51 US
cents Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency was traded within a narrow range and the
trade volume of the currency remained subdued during the day.
</P>
<P>
Traders said that international funds had flown out of the
country before the federal election. They expected the local
currency to remain at the current level in the next 24 hours.
</P>
