<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 08:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Mayor Stresses Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 1 (Xinhua) -- This largest industrial
center of China will strengthen environmental protection so that
"its sky and rivers will become cleaner" in the next five years.
</P>
<P>
"Economy can never be developed at the cost of environment and
ecology," Xu Kuangdi, Shanghai's mayor, told the city's leading
officials at a recent meeting.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the faster economy develops, the firmer people
should become in protecting environment.
</P>
<P>
During the Ninth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000), Shanghai
will improve the pattern of energy consumption by reducing coal
burning, he said.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to move some factories which tend to discharge
lots of waste liquid, waste gas or waste dregs out of the city's
inner ring, or upgrade them technologically or even order some to
shut down.
</P>
<P>
The mayor suggested that small machine tool factories be moved
into the Shanghai Machine Tool Plant which is located in an
outlying district covering two sq km.
</P>
<P>
Xu also called for more input into environmental protection in
order to launch a number of major environmental projects.
</P>
<P>
In dealing with the relationship between economic development
and environmental protection, the mayor said environmental
protection should co-ordinate with economic development.
</P>
<P>
"We must be responsible for our future generations and cannot
develop economy while ignoring environmental protection," the
mayor added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
