<HEADLINE> Fuel Prices Up In Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 1 (Xinhua)-- Zambia National Oil Company has
increased prices of petroleum products by 10 percent with
immediate effect, Zambia Daily Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
The daily quoted a statement of the company as saying that the
hikes followed a five percent levy on crude oil products announced in
this year's budget.
</P>
<P>
The other reason is the depreciation of the local currency kwacha,
which has affected the oil company's financial position for its crude
oil imports, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Price for per litre of premium fuel has risen to 0.63 US dollar
from the previous 0.57 dollar and that for diesel to 0.59 dollar from
0.54 dollar, according to the new price list. enditem

