<HEADLINE> 61 Schools Closed In Kampala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- A total of 61 privately owned
schools here have been closed by the Kampala City Council for
failing to meet basic requirements, according to an official
circular.
</P>
<P>
The circular released here today by the city's Education
Office said the closed schools had no toilet facilities and lacked
building furniture.
</P>
<P>
It added that more schools would be closed for the same resons
before the first term opens.
</P>
<P>
The affected schools would range from business institutions to
secondary, primary and nursery schools. 
</P>
