<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Sets April 12 For PNC Meeting In Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser
Arafat has disclosed that he selected April 12 to convene a
Palestine National Council (PNC) to begin discussions on annulling
sections of its covenant calling for the destruction of Israel.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who is both PLO Chairman and the Palestinian Authority
President-elected, made the disclosure at a meeting in Stockholm,
Sweden, Wednesday night with Israeli Deputy Foreign Minister Eli
Dayan, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
Israeli leaders have repeatedly warned that should the
Palestinian Authority fail to hold the PNC meeting to wipe out the
relevant clauses in the covenant within two months following the
Palestinian elections, the peace process would stop.
</P>
<P>
Arafat's adviser Ahmed Tibi said Tuesday that the articles in
question will be changed before Israel's elections, even if they
are moved up.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a group of senior officials at the Israeli army's
National Defense College, Tibi said that, on the one hand, the
dates for changing the covenant are "not holy," and on the other
hand, the commitment of PLO Chairman Yasser Arafat under Oslo 2
requires them to be abrogated.
</P>
<P>
"But you shouldn't stand there holding a stopwatch," said
Tibi, adding it is likely the abrogation of the covenant will take
place slightly after the agreed date.
</P>
<P>
Tibi noted that the abrogation of the covenant before the
elections would deprive the Likud of ammunition it was expecting
to use to attack the Labor-led government and the Oslo
agreements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
