<HEADLINE> Seles Books Quarter-Final Berth in Pan Pacific Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Top favorite Monica Seles nipped
Irina Spirlea on Thursday to book her quarter-final berth in the
Toray Pan Pacific Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Seles of the United States, who strained her left shoulder in
the Australian Open, scored her 6-4, 6-2 win over the Romanian.
</P>
<P>
In the first set, neither could break the other's game till a
4-all tie after deuces in the first five games.
</P>
<P>
Serving her ninth game, the 23rd-ranked Romanian committed a
double fault at 30-40, before Seles rushed to seal the first set
by keeping her own game intact.
</P>
<P>
Although Spirlea kept her two games first for 2-1 in the second
set, top seed Seles who co-ranked first in the world with Steffi
Graf, unleashed her powers to win the coming five games in a row.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Seles will play her quarter-final on Friday
against Iva Majoli of Croatia who beat Brenda Schultz-McCarthy of
the Netherlands 7-6 (8/6), 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain walked further even without
serving her game as Nicole Bradtke of Australia withdrew after she
strained her right foot in a doubles match Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Also winning their quarter-final spots were eighth-seed
American Lindsay Davenport and 15-year-old Swiss Martina Hingis.
</P>
<P>
Davenport smashed fellow American Lisa Raymond 6-1, 6-3 while
Hingis stunned Japanese Ai Sugiyama 6-0, 6-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
