<HEADLINE> Death Tolls In Uganda's Traffic Accidents Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The death tolls on Uganda's
roads rose 10 percent last year, reported the local daily the
Vision today.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, 1,416 people died in 1995, compared
to 1,289 in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the number of traffic accidents also increased
from 8,903 in 1994 to 12,058 in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The paper attributed the increase to taxi commuters who are
after money and do not care about people's lives.
</P>
<P>
Other reasons for the increase are careless and incompetent
driving.
</P>
<P>
However, the statistics revealed that the number of vehicles
involved in accidents in l995 were less than in l994.
</P>
</TEXT>
