<HEADLINE> More Vietnamese Migrants Back Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 1 (Xinhua) -- A group of 109 Vietnamese
migrants returned home today on the 29th flight under the Orderly
Repatriation Program (ORP).
</P>
<P>
Most of the returnees, comprising 62 men, 25 women and 22
children, arrived in Hong Kong in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Brian Bresnihan, the refugee coordinator, said that the
returnees on today's flight came forward voluntarily for the
transfer after counseling by Correctional Service Department.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,958 Vietnamese migrants have been repatriated on
ORP flights since November, 1991.  
