<HEADLINE> Drug Rehabilitation Center Helping Addicts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, February 1 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,300 drug addicts
in Shenzhen, the booming border city in south china's Guangdong
Province, were rehabilitated last year, thanks to treatment
provided by the local drug rehabilitation center, "Xinmin Evening
News" reports.
</P>
<P>
The center co-operated with a provincial drug campaign last
year, simplifying registration formalities and accepting drug
addicts at all hours, 513 of them coming from other parts of the
country, and 820 sent by public security departments.
</P>
<P>
There are different kinds of treatment available, such as
hypnotism therapy and comprehensive therapy.
</P>
<P>
A new treatment, the M-B united therapy, was tried out last
year, to alleviate suffering of addicts and helping them
recover. Those treated were in good health and had an average
weight increase of five kg when they left the center. 
</P>
