<HEADLINE> Beijing's Per Capita Consumption Grows 16.1 Percent in 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Per capita expenditure on
household items and services hit 442.51 yuan (about 53.3 US
dollars) here in 1995, an increase of 16.1 percent over 1994,
"Capital Economic Information Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
Expenditure on household items increased 324.36 yuan, an
increase of 12.1 percent over 1994. The steady rise is attributed
to the growth in the number of household items such as colour TVs,
refrigerators, and washing machines.
</P>
<P>
Although video cameras and personnel computers are becoming
more widespread, they are not entirely popular because of high
prices and limited use.
</P>
<P>
Air conditioners, electrical cooking items and household
electrical gadgets have become consumers' favorites.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in 1995, every 100 Beijing households
bought five air conditioners, an increase of 92.3 percent over
1994, and 8.4 electrical cooking items, a 1.5-fold increase.
</P>
<P>
There are 100.4 washing machines, 104.4 refrigerators, 113.6
colour TVs, 54.2 video recorders and players, 11.8 air
conditioners, 34 electrical cooking items, and 45.5 water heaters
for every 100 Beijing households.
</P>
<P>
In addition, per capita expenditures on decorations rose to
18.96 yuan, an increase of 49.3 percent over 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
