<HEADLINE> U.S. To Evacuate Diplomats From Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 31 (Xinhua) -- The United States has
decided to withdraw its diplomats and their families from Sudan, a
U.S. official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Some 30 Americans will be leaving the east African nation in
the next few days, said the official who spoke on condition of
anonymity.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken on the advice of the U.S. ambassador to
Sudan, who believed Sudan can no longer protect Americans against
extremist threats.
</P>
<P>
The official said the step was being taken only for security
reasons.
</P>
<P>
However, he stressed it was not a break in diplomatic relations
but a suspension of ties to Sudan.  
