<HEADLINE> DPRK Denounces South Korean, U.S. War Game Plans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) Wednesday denounced a series of planned
military exercises in South Korea.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the
Fatherland released a statement to denounce the war game plan as a
further provocation against the country.
</P>
<P>
The statement pointed to the fact that South Korea and the
United States have planned 30 percent more joint and separate
military drills than last year's total.
</P>
<P>
South Korea and the United States held a joint military
exercise at sea earlier this year while the two countries have
also planned to stage three more joint war games codenamed
"Freedom Banner," "Ulji Focus Lens" and "Foal Eagle."
</P>
<P>
South Korea plans to stage this year two separate drills
codenamed as "Hoguk" and "Hwarang."
</P>
<P>
The reunification committee said that South Korea is resorting
to its theory of "Threats From the North" to justify its military
drills and to shift the responsibility for the tense situation on
the Korean peninsula onto the DPRK. 
</P>
