promulgated a law recently to protect domestic consumers'
interests.
</P>
<P>
Under the law, counterfeit and shoddy goods are not allowed to
be imported and sold in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Violators will be fined and sued and those who seriously
violate the law will be sentenced to a maximum of 10 years'
imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
As soon as the law came out, it won warm welcome from the
consumers in the country.
</P>
<P>
Islami Cani, head of the Albanian Consumers' Association, told
Xinhua that it is very necessary for the government to enact the
law because the domestic market currently is out of control.
</P>
<P>
He added that outdated and counterfeit food products as well as
some with radioactive substances have badly infringed upon
consumers' interests. 
</P>
