<HEADLINE> New Type Vehicle Developed in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 31 (Xinhua) -- The Renault Automobile Company
has succeeded in developing a new type of battery-gasoline
powered vehicle that will reduce gas emissions.
</P>
<P>
A sample of this type named NEXT was put on show here recently.
</P>
<P>
NEXT has a small gasoline engine installed in the front of its
body and two storage batteries on the axle of rear wheels.
</P>
<P>
The new type vehicle, driven by battery power at a speed under
40 kilometers an hour (k/h), will help eliminate gas pollution in
urban districts.
</P>
<P>
When the speed goes beyond 40 k/h, the gasoline engine will
supply the automobile with power while storage batteries will be
charged.
</P>
<P>
This new type of vehicle meets the criteria of low pollution
and high speed. Driven by both kinds of engines, its maximum speed
will exceed 167 kilometers per hour. 
</P>
