<HEADLINE> Money World Asia Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Money World Asia -- Hong Kong
'96, jointly organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council
(TDC), and Money World Asia (HK) Ltd, opened here today.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, Frederick Lam, deputy executive
director of TDC, said that Hong Kong is the ideal location for a
new international trade fair focusing on money, investment and
financial services.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong ranks as the world's 11th largest
exporter of commercial services and is widely recognized as a
strategic center for banking and financial services.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, about 80 of the almost 200 financial
institutions incorporated in Hong Kong are among the world's top
100 banks.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is also home to Asia's second largest stock exchange,
and the world's fifth largest foreign exchange market,
third-largest gold bullion market and seventh largest foreign
currency holding.
</P>
<P>
As the first of its kind held in Hong Kong, the four-day fair
features a comprehensive range of financial services and
money-related products, including consumer and corporate banking,
equity investment, fund management, commodities and forex trading,
and money collectibles, presented by over 150 exhibitors from
across the region.
</P>
<P>
Lam said that strong presence from the stock exchanges of
Shanghai, Shenzhen, Singapore and Thailand together with their
member companies, regulatory authorities and financial
institutions, including a large delegation led by the People's
Bank of China, represented a resounding vote of confidence in this
inaugural event.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, there is an investors' forum with a series of
seminars and presentations to update institutional investors on
latest investment environment and opportunities across the region.
</P>
<P>
</P>
