<HEADLINE> 200 Dhaka University Students Injured in Clash  with Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to sources concerned this morning, the clash erupted
when activists of the pro-Awami (people's) League, the largest
opposition party in the country, came into a violent clash with
pro-government student organization over the visit of Prime
Minister Begum Khaleda Zia in the university campus scheduled for
this morning. The clash occurred following a dispute over the
inauguration of a traditional book fair, they added.
</P>
<P>
