<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Two suspects responsible for
Wednesday's bomb blast in front of Sri Lanka Central Bank in
downtown Colombo have been arrested, police sources said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The two suspects, Ragu and Dharma Ruben, are members of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) who came from Killinochchi
in North-Central Province where the headquarters of the LTTE is
said to be situated.
</P>
<P>
The two were arrested while trying to make their getaway after
disposing of four grenades, a suicide kit equipped with a push
button, two home-made bombs, two magazines and two walkie- talkies
at a bakery in central Colombo, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The two were among the four-member LTTE suicide squad which
carried out the bomb attack that damaged a number of high rises
and left about 100 people dead and over 1,400 others injured, the
sources said.  
