<HEADLINE> Unemployment Down Slightly in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Almost one in 10 working-age
people still remains unemployed in Romania despite the downward
trend that started in January last year.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics as of January 22 this year said one million
people were out of work, accounting for 8.9 percent of the
country's total workforce.
</P>
<P>
But the figure was 1.6 percentage points lower than last year's.
</P>
<P>
More than half of the jobless are women. Some 772,000 of the
jobless can get unemployment relief which equals to one third of
the national average of the monthly workers wages.
</P>
<P>
Romania is encouraging the development of small and
medium-sized enterprises by providing them with low-interest loans
in the hope that these developing business will help create more
jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
