being negotiated by Mexico and Central American countries,
according to Naranjo.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica has already signed such an agreement with Mexico,
which was put into effect last year.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the countries will also discuss issues of trade,
investment, financial and banking relations, stock markets and
immigration.
</P>
<P>
