<HEADLINE> Belarus Favors Close Integration With Russia: Lukashenko </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MINSK, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Belarussian President Alexander
Lukashenko said today that his country favors a close integration
with Russia and firmly opposes the NATO plan to expand eastward.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov who
arrived here Tuesday on a visit, Lukashenko said Belarus and
Russia have quickened the steps in realizing their integration by
working out a series of relevant accords.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have also laid down the legal foundation for
the implementation of these agreements, he said.
</P>
<P>
As for the NATO's eastward expansion, the two sides repeated
their rejection of such a move.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko stressed that the countries concerned should seek a
solution acceptable to all sides through consultations because the
NATO expansion will give rise to a number of problems. 
</P>
