<HEADLINE> Over 3 Million People Out of Work in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 31 (Xinhua) -- France today reported an increase
of 57,600 jobless people in November and December with the total
exceeding 3 million by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The total of unemployed people was 3,019,400 at the end of
1995, down 1.9 percent from the figure a year earlier, according
to statistics from the French Labor Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The figure was released one day after the government announced
some measures to stimulate the economy, which was throttled by a
nationwide strike at the end of November and in December last
year. 
