<HEADLINE> EU Sets Key Sectors for Scientific Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Five key areas for scientific
research were today approved by the Commission of the European
Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
The Commission said that aviation and aerospace, educational
multi-media software, pollution-safe vehicles, multi-mean
transport systems and environmental protection techniques were
all vital for the EU's future strength.
</P>
<P>
The body wants the 700 million ECU (569 million U.S. dollars)
reserve fund of the EU's 12.3 billion ECU (10 billion dollars)
fourth scientific research program to be used mainly for these
sectors to allow research projects to move ahead more quickly.
</P>
<P>
The resolution is to be submitted to the Council of Europe and
the EU's Council of Ministers for further approval.
</P>
<P>
There is strong market potential in the EU for the five key
areas and member countries are more likely to coordinate
policy-making in these areas, the commission said.
</P>
<P>
Development will also help create jobs and benefit a number of
economic sectors and regions, the commission added.
</P>
<P>
It estimates that in the aviation and aerospace industries
alone, some 7,000 businesses employ around 400,000 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
