<HEADLINE> French General Takes Office as Eurocorps' New Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 31 (Xinhua) -- French Lieutenant General Pierre
Forterre today succeeded German General Helmut Willmann as the new
commander of the 50,000-strong Eurocorps.
</P>
<P>
At a hand-over ceremony held in the northeastern French city of
Strasburg, where Eurocorps headquarters stands, Forterre said he
will be much concerned about the unit's ability to deal with
crises.
</P>
<P>
A rapid reaction force, with 2,000 to 4,000 soldiers, will be
created for humanitarian actions, with an exercise to be held this
year in Spain, the 55-year-old general said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, a mechanized force equipped with heavy
weapons has also been envisaged.
</P>
<P>
The Eurocorps, which comprises troops from France, Germany,
Belgium, Spain and Luxembourg, was declared operational on
November 30, 1995 following a large-scale military exercise.
</P>
<P>
Placed at the disposal of the Western European Union and, in
case of serious conflict, the force aims to defend NATO and
implement United Nations peacekeeping missions and actions of
humanitarian aid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
