<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Central Bank Vault Intact, Official Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan Central Bank's vault
which holds the country's cash and gold reserves is intact and
safe, an official of the bank said here today.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the vault in the basement of the
building had not been affected by the bomb blast Wednesday which
had damaged the entire Central Bank Building and nearby
high-rises.
</P>
<P>
Some cash in the issuing counter on the ground floor might have
got displaced in the blast, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, the entire area has been declared out of bounds to
ensure the safety of whatever cash that may be strewn about, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The official also said that all the top officials of the bank
including Governor A. S. Jayawardena were safe.
</P>
<P>
The massive vehicle bomb blast in front of the Central Bank
left about 100 people dead and over 1,400 injured.  
</P>
