<HEADLINE> Bulgarian President Critical of His Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian President Zheliu Zhelev
today criticized the ruling Socialist Party as incompetent and
inefficient, urging a snap election to overhaul the cabinet.
</P>
<P>
He told a press briefing that the Socialist Party-led
government poses a menace to the country's security, interest and
future.
</P>
<P>
Zhelev, chairman of the Cooperative Committee of the Union of
the Democratic Forces of Bulgaria, read out a 30-minute speech
fully critical of the year-long reign of Prime Minister Zhan
Videnov, who is the leader of the Socialist Party.
</P>
<P>
The president cited decreasing overseas investment as the
severest failure of the Videnov cabinet. He said that in 1995
foreign investment was less than one-tenth of the total promised
by Videnov before he took office and 1.5 times less than the 1994
level.
</P>
<P>
Zhelev accused the Videnov government of failing to run state
affairs in a professional and responsible way.
</P>
<P>
