<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 02:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cultural Relics Protection Projects in Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 27.75 million yuan (3.24
million US dollars) has been spent on conservation and protection
of cultural relics in northwest China's Shaanxi Province over the
past five years.
</P>
<P>
The investment is 3.3 times that of the previous five years,
and was used for 89 historical buildings, sites and tombs,
including the mausoleum of Huangdi, Chinese first emperor, and
that of Emperor Gaozong and Empress Wu Zetian of the Tang
(618-907).
</P>
<P>
The province was a political and cultural center for China's
early dynasties, and was mostly famous during the Han (206 BC-AD
220) and Tang dynasties. It has 37 historical sites that are under
state protection, the largest number of any province.
</P>
<P>
In the next five years, more investment will be put into
protecting cultural relics, mainly large ancient capital and
palace ruins and 13 old revolutionary sites in Yan'an, to
commemorate the 60th anniversary of the Chinese Communist Party's
marching into Yan'an in January 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960201.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 02:05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Tap Natural Gas in Qaidam Basin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The China National Petroleum
Corporation (CNPC) is cooperating with Amoco in tapping natural
gas in Qinghai Province's Qaidam Basin.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement signed recently, the American company
will carry out six months of exploration and evaluation in a
21,000-sq-km area in the eastern part of the basin, and has rights
to develop and transport gas, and use refined products.
</P>
<P>
Known as a "treasure bowl", the basin abounds in lake salt,
potash, oil, asbestos, lead, zinc, and other minerals.
</P>
<P>
Geologists have predicted that the volume of natural gas totals
one trillion cubic meters, ranking among the country's greatest.
</P>
<P>
Proven gas reserves amount to 50 billion cubic meters, are
close to the surface, and are under high pressure with a high
percentage of methane.
</P>
<P>
At present, the oil field in the basin has an annual oil
production capacity of 1.25 million tons and oil-refinery capacity
of 800,000 tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
