<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 01:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile's Exports To EU Increase 54 Percent In 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Chile's exports to the
European Union (EU) increased by 54 percent to reach a record high
in 1995, a government institution called Prochile said today.
</P>
<P>
Exports to EU earned Chile 4.363 billion U.S. dollars last
year, accounting for 26 percent of the country's total export
earnings, according to Prochile.
</P>
<P>
The country's total export earnings last year stood at 16.453
billion dollars, which represented a 41 percent increase over the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Chile's exports to the South American Common Market, known
in spanish as MERCOSUR for short, increased by 31 percent to reach
1.772 billion dollars last year. Chile has applied to join
MERCOSUR, which now embraces Brazil, Uruguay, Argentina and
Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
Chile's exports to the three countries of the North American
Free Trade Agreement last year also showed a moderate increase of
13 percent over 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
