history.
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily (overseas edition)"
</P>
<P>
-- An official with the Office for Taiwan Affairs of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council urged compatriots on
both sides of the Taiwan Straits to unite and make an effort to
reunify the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came on the first anniversary of President Jiang
Zemin's speech entiled "Continue to Promote the Reunification of
the Motherland".
</P>
<P>
The official said that the principle of "reunifying the
motherland peacefully and one country, two systems" must be
carried out, and "Taiwan independence", "two Chinas", and "one
China, one Taiwan" must be opposed firmly.
</P>
<P>
