in northwest China's Qinghai Province were rescued to safe places
by army soldiers.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- A central bank spokesman yesterday ruled out the possibility
of relaxing monetary control and reiterated that the appropriately
tight monetary policy will be kept firmly in place this year.
</P>
<P>
Ma Delun, spokesman for the People's Bank of China, told a
press conference that the broad money supply is still high and
price increases have kept a two-digit pace. 
