<DOCNO> XIE19960201.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 01:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Russia Increases in 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in Russia
reached a record high of more than 2 billion U.S. dollars in 1995,
twice as much as in 1994, the State Statistical Committee said
today.
</P>
<P>
Total foreign investment since 1991 had reached 6 billion
dollars by early October last year, with about half the total
invested between 1991 and 1993, figures from the committee show.
</P>
<P>
Of the foreign investment in 1995, 14.7 percent went to the
commerce and food sectors, 13 percent to finance, credit and
insurance, and 10.4 percent to the fuel industry.
</P>
<P>
Attracting foreign investment still remains one of the
government's main objectives, in spite of the recent cabinet
reshuffle and a shift in foreign policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
