<HEADLINE> Gordeeva to Play Solo in Tribute Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Ekaterina Gordeeva, former
world and Olympic pairs champion, said on Wednesday she will
return to the ice next month to pay tribute to her late husband
and skating partner Sergei Grinkov.
</P>
<P>
However, Gordeeva will perform solo in the February 27 show in
Connecticut.
</P>
<P>
The show attracts the participation of former world champions
Kurt Browning, Katarina Witt and Brian Boitano, with the proceeds
for a fund to help the 25-year-old Gordeeva and her three-year-old
daughter Daria.
</P>
<P>
At the age of 28, Grinkov died last November 20 of heart attack
during a practice session with his wife in New York.
</P>
<P>
The husband-wife pair won the Olympic golds both at Calgary in
1988 and at Lillehammer in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
