<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 01:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Muster to Steal Top Spot for First Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Thomas Muster of Austria will
snatch the world's top spot for the first time in his career when
the latest ATP rankings to be announced on February 12.
</P>
<P>
Muster, winner of 12 tournaments in 1995 including the French
Open, will have 4,474 points, enough for him to take over Andre
Agassi of 4,379 to claim the top spot.
</P>
<P>
Thus, Muster will become the 13th player to hold the number one
spot, but he will face strong challenge in a week time from a trio
of Boris Becker, Andre Agassi and Pete Sampras.
</P>
<P>
Agassi replaced Sampras at the top during the Australian Open
last week. However, he will be stripped of the honour as the ATP
will not account for the 206 points he won in San Jose last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
