<HEADLINE> South Africa Makes Final in African Nations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 31 (Xinhua) -- John Mosheou scored twice
to pace the hosts South Africa for a 3-0 semi-final victory over
Ghana on Wednesday at the African Nations Cup tournament.
</P>
<P>
With the two netted, Mosheou ranked second in the scorers' list
on four, next to Kalusha Bwalya of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Moshoeu opened the scoring in the 22nd minute with a kick from
Doctor Khumalo's corner, and netted his second two minutes before
the whistle blew.
</P>
<P>
The other goal was slammed home by Sean Bartlett one minute
after the break from a long pass off Lucas Radebe.
</P>
<P>
The hosts had dominated the green pitch for the most part of
the game with tight defense and ground-breaking attacks from the
mid-field, forcing their opponents to resort to counter-attacks.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, South Africa will vie for the title on
February 3 against Tunisia that eliminated Zambia 4-2 in the other
semifinal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
