<HEADLINE> Greece's New Government Wins Confidence Vote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Greek Prime Minister Costas
simitis and his new government received a vote of confidence from
parliament early this mornong, with 166 deputies in the 300-seat
house supporing the motion.
</P>
<P>
The 123 opposition deputies all voted against, while three
deputies, including two from ruling party PASOK abstained. eight
deputies were absent.
</P>
<P>
The vote of confidence came after a three-day debate, beginning
with simitis presentation of the government's policy statement on
Monday night and amidst tension with Turkey in the Aegean.
</P>
<P>
Simitis received a mandate to form a government from President
Kostis Stephanopoulos late last week, shortly after being elected
by ruling party deputies to replace ailing PASOK leader Andreas
Papandreou as prime minister. 
</P>
