<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-36 23:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Council Urges Sudan to Extradite Terrorist Suspects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 31 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security
Council on Wednesday urged Sudan to extradite to Ethiopia for
prosecution of three suspects involved in an assassination attempt
against Egyptian President Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
It is the second time the Security Council has made such an
appeal to Sudan. Earlier this month, the council issued a
presidential statement to this effect.
</P>
<P>
The assassination attempt on the life of President Mubarak
happened on June 26,1995, when the Organization of African Unity
(OAU) convened a summit meeting in Ethipia's capitol Addis Ababa.
Mubarak was shot at by terrorists on his way to hotel from the
airport.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia later arrested several suspects and found out that
three suspects are hiding out in Sudan. It demanded through OAU
that Sudan surrender the three suspects.
</P>
<P>
A resolution, which was adopted by the council unanimously,
called upon Sudan to comply with the requests of OAU without
further delay.
</P>
<P>
Firstly it must undertake immediate action to extradite to
Ethiopia for prosecution the three suspects.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, it must desist from engaging in activities of
assisting, supporting and facilitating terrorist activities and
from giving shelter to terrorist elements.
</P>
<P>
The council also urged the international community to encourage
Sudan to respond fully and effectively to the OAU requests.
</P>
<P>
In an explanation speech to the council before it adopted the
resolution, Sudan's permanent representative to the United
Nations, denied the charges that Sudan was sheltering terrorists.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Ali Yassin said his country condemned in the
strongest terms the assassination attempt against the Egyptian
President.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Sudan was always ready to cooperate fully with
with the secretary general of the OAU in accordance with the OAU
and United Nations Charters and the norms of international law.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Permanent Representative to the United Nations Qin
Huasun said the Chinese government has always strongly opposed and
condemned acts of terrorism in all its forms, for they not only
endanger innocent lives and social stability, but also pose a
threat to international security.
</P>
<P>
"We sincerely hope that the OAU, with the support of the
Security Council, will continue to play its due important role in
bringing about a poor solution to this incident," he said.
</P>
<P>
But he stressed that in addressing this act of terrorism as in
other international disputes, the council should be careful,
serious and prudent when taking any actions.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, we have reservation on elements in (b) of
operative paragraph 4 of the text calling upon Sudan to desist
from engaging in activities of assisting, supporting and
conniving at terrorist activities," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Listen to all sides and you will be enlightened; otherwise
you will be benighted," he said, hoping the council to fully
listen to the views of the parties concerned and the OAU and
give play to their role as much as possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
