<HEADLINE> New York Stocks March to New Highs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, January 31 (Xinhua) -- Stocks at the New York Stock
Exchange climbed to new highs for the fourth session in a row,
after the Federal Reserve came through with a widely expected cut
in short-term interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 13.73 points to 5,394.94.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues led decliners by nearly 2 to 1, with 1,578 up,
824 down and 712 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Transition volume totaled 472.06 million shares, up from 464.33
million Tuesday.
</P>
