<HEADLINE> New Bosnian Federal Government Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB,January 31 (Xinhua) -- The parliament of Bosnian
Federation on Wednesday approved the new federal government which
will reign over territories controlled by Muslims and Croats.
</P>
<P>
Headed by federal prime minister Izudin Kapetanovic, the new
government consists of 14 ministers in charge of defense,
interior, justice, industry, transport, health, education, trade,
environment and other internal affairs of the federation.
</P>
<P>
Kresimir Zubak, the federal president who submitted the list,
said that the new government is formed by experts of whom there
are six with doctoral degrees, two masters of science, four
economists, four electrical engineers, three lawyers and two
medical doctors. The average age of Government officials is 46.
</P>
<P>
Of the 14 government ministers, seven are Muslims, six Croats
and one Serb.
</P>
<P>
Under terms of the Bosnian peace agreement, the country
consists of the two identities, namely the Muslim-Croat federation
and the Serb republic.
</P>
<P>
The functions of the old federal government which was headed by
former prime minister Harris Silajdzic overlapped with those of the
Bosnian central government. The new one is supposed to deal with
internal affairs of the federation, while the central government will
take care of foreign affairs, foreign trade and monetary polcies of
the whole country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
