<HEADLINE> UN Extends Mission for Referendum in W. Sahara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 31 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Security Council decided today to extend the mandate of the United
Nations Mission for the Referendum in Western Sahara (MINURSO)
until May 31, 1996.
</P>
<P>
In a resolution adopted unanimously today, the council
expressed deep concern about the stalemate which has been
hindering the identification process and the consequent lack of
progress towards completion of the Settlement Plan.
</P>
<P>
It called upon both the government of Morocco and the Polisario
Front of Western Sahara to cooperate with Secretary-General
Boutros Boutros-Ghali and MINURSO in resuming the identification
process, overcoming obstacles hindering completion of that
process, and implementing all other aspects of the Settlement
Plan.
</P>
<P>
Western Sahara in Northwest Africa was taken under Spanish
protection in 1884 and became a Spanish province in 1958. Its
neighbouring countries Morocco and Mauritania pressured Spain to
relinquish the area in the early 1960s and the Polisario Front
fought for independence from 1973. After Spanish withdrew in 1976
and Mauritania signed a treaty with Polisario renouncing its
claims in 1979, Morocco announced annexation of the entire area.
</P>
<P>
With help of U.N. secretary-general and the the Organization of
African Unity, Morocco and Polisario Front signed a document
referred to as the settlement proposals in 1988. According to the
document, the people of Western Sahara would choose between
independence and integration with Morocco in the exercise of their
right to self-determination.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council established MINURSO in 1991 to verify the
case-fire and cessation of hostilities, identify and register
qualified voters; and organize and ensure a free referendum.
</P>
<P>
According to the settlement plan, the referendum in Western
Sahara should have taken place in January 1992. However, the
referendum has been postponed again and and again because of their
differences on voter eligibility, release of political prisoners
and other issues.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960201.0272 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-36 21:38 </DATE_TIME>
