<HEADLINE> Japan Donates Books To Nigerian University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government has
donated 34 volumes of books worth about 25.82 million naira (some
300,000 U.S. dollars) to the Lagos State University (LASU).
</P>
<P>
The donation was made through the Japanese Foundation,
established primarily to promote international cultural
exchanges.
</P>
<P>
A statement by the Japanese embassy here today said that the
donation was part of the foundation's 1995 library support
program.
</P>
<P>
The gift, which includes books on economics, business,
history, politics and Japanese law, is the second by the
foundation to LASU and the seventeenth to institutions in
Nigeria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
