<HEADLINE> Moussa Urges Sudan to Stop Harboring Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa today described the latest U.N. resolution on Sudan as an
important message, urging Sudan to "stop harboring terrorism."
</P>
<P>
The Middle East News Agency said Amr Moussa called on the
Sudanese authorities to reassess its policies.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Security Council adopted a resolution Wednesday
calling on Sudan to extradite three men wanted by Ethiopia for an
assassination attempt on Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in Addis
Ababa last June.
</P>
<P>
Moussa said that the Arab, African and international
communities reject the Sudanese policies despite Sudan's attempts
to deny them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
