<HEADLINE> Nigerian Medical Doctors On Nationwide Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's medical doctors today
started a nationwide strike to press for improved working
conditions and a 15 per cent increase of their salaries.
</P>
<P>
Doctors were not on duty at the Lagos University Teaching
Hospital, where they joined the strike called by the National
Association of Resident Doctors.
</P>
<P>
The situation was similar at the Psychiatric Hospital and
the National Orthopaedic Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Last November, the doctors went on strike for similar reason
but called it off five days later, following a government promise
to meet their demands in three months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
