<DATE_TIME> 1996-02-01 20:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Economic Forum Opens in Davos, Switzerland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAVOS, Switzerland, February 1 (Xinhua) -- World Economic Forum
opened its 1996 session this afternoon in the small Swiss town of
Davos with an agenda focusing on the opportunities and challenges
of economic globalization.
</P>
<P>
The six-day gathering in the eastern Swiss mountain resort
brings together about 1,000 business leaders, over 600 political
leaders and public figures worldwide for discussions on world
issues and international economic trends.
</P>
<P>
This year the theme was set as "sustaining globalization". As
the founder and president of the Forum Klaus Schwab put it, "Today
globalization has become an irreversible fact and is very often
made the scapegoat for many social problems".
</P>
<P>
The globalization process is posing great challenges to
developed and developing counytries alike, creating uncertainty
among nations and a backlash from those negatively affected, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Business and political leaders present at the Forum will look
at the policies needed in this new global environment to reduce
the level of uncertainty and restore trust, Schwab said.
</P>
<P>
As in the past the Forum this year will also cover a number of
regional issues. Highlights on the agenda include the peace
process in the Middle East, reconstruction of the Former
Yugoslavia, the European integration, as well as elections later
this year both in the United States and Russia.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian President Yasser Arafat, Israeli Prime Minister
Shimon Peres, prime ministers of Bosnia, Croatia and the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia, and presidents from Argentina, Mexico and
Peru are among the political leaders attending the Forum.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of international economic institutions such as Director
General Renato Ruggiero of the World Trade Organization, President
James Wolfenson of the World Bank, and Stanley Fischer, First
Deputy Managing Director of the International Monetary Fund are
also present at this year's Forum.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
